│ 13587 /// Merges shuffle masks and emits final shuffle instruction, if required. It                                                                                                                            │
│ 13588 /// supports shuffling of 2 input vectors. It implements lazy shuffles emission,                                                                                                                         │
│ 13589 /// when the actual shuffle instruction is generated only if this is actually                                                                                                                            │
│ 13590 /// required. Otherwise, the shuffle instruction emission is delayed till the                                                                                                                            │
│ 13591 /// end of the process, to reduce the number of emitted instructions and further                                                                                                                         │
│ 13592 /// analysis/transformations.                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ 13593 /// The class also will look through the previously emitted shuffle instructions                                                                                                                         │
│ 13594 /// and properly mark indices in mask as undef.                                                                                                                                                          │
│ 13595 /// For example, given the code                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ 13596 /// \code                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 13597 /// %s1 = shufflevector <2 x ty> %0, poison, <1, 0>                                                                                                                                                      │
│ 13598 /// %s2 = shufflevector <2 x ty> %1, poison, <1, 0>                                                                                                                                                      │
│ 13599 /// \endcode                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ 13600 /// and if need to emit shuffle of %s1 and %s2 with mask <1, 0, 3, 2>, it will                                                                                                                           │
│ 13601 /// look through %s1 and %s2 and emit                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ 13602 /// \code                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 13603 /// %res = shufflevector <2 x ty> %0, %1, <0, 1, 2, 3>                                                                                                                                                   │
│ 13604 /// \endcode                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ 13605 /// instead.                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ 13606 /// If 2 operands are of different size, the smallest one will be resized and                                                                                                                            │
│ 13607 /// the mask recalculated properly.                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ 13608 /// For example, given the code                                                                                                                                                                          │
